    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philada</placeName>
                <date>Octr 3 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Three hundred copies of the<lb/> “Geography of
                    <placeName>Palestine</placeName>” having been disposed<lb/> of to this date. I
                send <sic>inclosed</sic> Forty-five<lb/> Dollars for your copyright on that no.
                of<lb/> copies. I also beg your acceptance of the<lb/> offering ($25) made to you in
                the Synagogue<lb/> on the <date>1st day of “Roshashana”</date> &amp; which I
                should<lb/> have sent before Had I not been absent<lb/> from the City immediately
                thereafter &amp; on my<lb/> return it escaped my memory till this moment.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Trusting that your health is reinstated<lb/> and that you may
                hereafter enjoy that<lb/> first of blessings together with all the<lb/> happiness
                this life affords, is the sincere<lb/> wish of    Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">A Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <p>To the <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">(Ck enclosed on the Philad Bank for $70)</p>
        </body>
    </text>
